---
// Two-door chooser — competitor research 2026-07-19 (medium/M flow):
// GoLive splits traffic at the top ('Shop Templates' vs 'Hire Our Team')
// so no one bounces for being the wrong budget. Our SiteGuide downshift
// only appeared far below the fold (Services card 3, FAQ, Footer) — this
// puts the fork one scroll from the Hero. The dedicated /siteguide page
// with template previews is deferred until real preview assets exist
// (SiteGuide lane owns the screenshot capture); the door links out to the
// live demo storefront instead, on its own UTM lane.
---

<section class="relative py-10 sm:py-14" aria-label="Two ways to get a site">
  <div class="container-page">
    <div class="reveal mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="hairline"></span>
      <p class="kicker mono">Two ways in</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <!-- Door 1 — custom build lane, lands in the on-page intake -->
      <a
        href="#intake"
        class="group panel flex flex-col gap-2 p-6 transition-colors hover:bg-ink-soft/60"
        data-cta="door-custom"
        data-section="two-door"
        data-intent="book:free-review"
      >
        <span class="mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-clay/80">→ Built for you</span>
        <p class="font-medium text-bone">Custom site, one engineer, from $500</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-bone-dim">
          Scoped, shipped, and handed off — no agency middlemen. Starts with the
          free video teardown below.
        </p>
      </a>

      <!-- Door 2 — sub-$500 template lane, routes to SiteGuide instead of bouncing -->
      <a
        href="https://siteguide-production.up.railway.app/demos?utm_source=m3mm&utm_medium=two-door&utm_campaign=downshift&utm_content=hero-two-door"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="group panel flex flex-col gap-2 p-6 transition-colors hover:bg-ink-soft/60"
        data-cta="door-siteguide"
        data-section="two-door"
        data-intent="product:siteguide"
      >
        <span class="mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-cyber/80">→ Fast and cheap</span>
        <p class="font-medium text-bone">Off-the-shelf template, under $500</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-bone-dim">
          Twelve one-page SiteGuide templates you can preview + buy today, with a
          clean upgrade path into a custom M3 site later.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
